DESCRIPTION:Image credit: Smit Zaveri and Barkha Lohia\nThrough imagined letters and storytelling\, Haru’s Paper Garden sheds light on the life of Vishnuprasad\, an artist whose contributions remain largely unrecorded.\n\nIn this reading and activity session\, author Smit Zaveri invites young audiences to think about art\, memory and the stories that history forgets.
